      • propagateOverGraph

        public static <T> GraphPropagation<T> propagateOverGraph(Graph<T> graph,
                                                         GraphNodeSearchInterface<T> gnsi,
                                                         GraphPropagationEffectController<T> effectController,
                                                         GraphPropagationDirectionController<T> directionController,
                                                         boolean raiseExceptionOnInvalidNode,
                                                         boolean treatGraphDirectionally)
                                                  throws PropagationException
        Propagates over the graph with the specified controller and starting node
        Parameters:
        graph - a graph over which to propagate
        gnsi - an interface with which to find the start node
        effectController - controller to regulate the effect of the propagation
        directionController - controller to regulate the direction of the propagation
        raiseExceptionOnInvalidNode - if 'true' will raise an exception if a discovered node is invalid
        treatGraphDirectionally - if 'true' will propagate with respect to the direction of the edges
        Returns:
        the propagation used
        Throws:
        PropagationException - if an invalid node is encountered and the 'raiseExceptionOnInvalidNode' is true. Also if the controller raises an exception to the invocation
